Methods

Image acquisition

All images of the Lepidoptera were pulled from the Global Biodiversity Information Facility (GBIF), a clearing house of collections and species information. GBIF have created an R package, rgif, that allows access to GBIF’s application programming interface (API).This packages allows their records to be searchable from the command line.

library(rgbif)

Roughly 200 species of Lepidoptera

Results

Evolutionary Rates

forewing.pca <- forewings %>%
  coo_interpolate(fore.min) %>%
  coo_align()  %>%
  coo_slide(id=1) %>% 
  fgProcrustes() %>% 
  efourier(norm=FALSE) %>% 
  PCA()

hindwing.pca <-hindwings %>% 
  coo_interpolate(hind.min) %>% 
  coo_align()  %>%
  coo_slide(id=1) %>% 
  fgProcrustes() %>% 
  efourier(norm=FALSE) %>% 
  PCA()

Finding evolutionary rates for fore- and hindwing PCs.

library(phytools)
forePC1.BM<-brownie.lite(lep.tree2,fore.pc1*10)
hindPC1.BM<-brownie.lite(lep.tree2,hind.pc1*10)

forePC2.BM<-brownie.lite(lep.tree2,fore.pc2*10)
hindPC2.BM<-brownie.lite(lep.tree2,hind.pc2*10)
#Compare PC1 wing evolutionary rates
forePC1.BM$sig2.single
## [1] 0.006535527
hindPC1.BM$sig2.single
## [1] 0.01014157
#Compare PC2 wing evolutionary rates
forePC2.BM$sig2.single
## [1] 0.002411568
hindPC2.BM$sig2.single
## [1] 0.01870921

Using the “noncensored test,” analysis showed that the rates of wing-shape evolution between the fore- and hindwings were different. In PC1, the difference was 0.003606043 units. In PC2, the difference was 0.016297642 units.

Evolutionary Rate Shifts

Lepidoptera phylogenetic tree with lineages with exceptional shifts indicated by a triangle. Blue and downward triangle signifies a low shift. 

## # A tibble: 1 × 4
##       n rate.difference p.value clade                      
##   <dbl>           <dbl>   <dbl> <chr>                      
## 1   225        -0.00194   0.001 Macroheterocera: Noctuoidea

The Macroheterocera clade, specifically the Noctuoidea family underwent a significant shift in evolutionary rate, with a slowdown of -0.00194 units.

Analysis of fore- and hindwing PC1 shows that they are correlated. The p-value is very close to zero, indicating a significant relationship. Additionally, the R-squared value is 0.44. However, fore- and hindwing PC2s are not correlated. The p-value is 0.4121 and R-squared value is very low.
